<b>European Spatial Planning Research and Information Database</b> (<it>ESPRID</it>) is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../311/288311.xml">
web-based</link> Information Resource (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../377/8377.xml">
database</link>) managed at <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../338/203338.xml">
Newcastle University</link></university>
.<p>

It provides a search platform for those interested in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../693/860693.xml">
Spatial development</link> Analysis, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../010/378010.xml">
Planning</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../091/375091.xml">
policy</link> but especially <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../607/29607.xml">
Strategic</link> Spatial Planning in a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../239/9239.xml">
Europe</link>an context. In the context of the contemporary devolution processes and the growing application of the <work wordnetid="100575741" confidence="0.8">
<examination wordnetid="100635850" confidence="0.8">
<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
